Hi!
> > Well, maybe it is better than requiring ext2cap, reiserfscap, vfatcap,
> > isocap, udfcap and nfscap :-).
> 
> You'll want capabilities in your attached filessystems, at most. So yes, it
> will have to be in ext3fs and reiserfs. But not in ISO, VFAT or even NFS or
> CODA.
If capabilities are not present on ISO, how are you going to install
your system. If you don't have capabilities on NFS, how secure are
your workstations going to be?
